I think this is because of the master-detail.

I just created a simple sample, and I can track the event even if it leaves the view. I then put it into a master-detail page, and then the events stopped as soon as I moved horizontally.

I am not sure if this is a bug with the Xamarin.Forms master-detail page hijacking events mid way, or if it is an issue with the SkiaSharp view. I will investigate further, but in the meantime, I managed to stop the gestures with `IsGestureEnabled = false`:

```csharp
void Handle_Touch(object sender, SKTouchEventArgs e)
{
	if (e.ActionType == SKTouchAction.Pressed)
	{
		// disable gestures when we start dragging
		var md = Application.Current.MainPage as MasterDetailPage;
		md.IsGestureEnabled = false;
	}

	// handle usual touch events

	if (e.ActionType == SKTouchAction.Released)
	{
		// re-enable gestures when we are finished
		var md = Application.Current.MainPage as MasterDetailPage;
		md.IsGestureEnabled = true;
	}
}
```
